= RML Data Display Elements =

== DATAGRID Element ==

''Attributes''[[br]]
'''source = [wiki:documentation/Glossary#BasicTypes datasource]''' [wiki:documentation/Glossary#CaseInformation (CS)]
  The name of the data source and table that the rows of the data grid will be fetched from.

=== COL Element ===

The ''COL'' represents a column in the datagrid. Each column displays information about each row in the data source in the form of one or more fields.

''Attributes''[[br]]
'''fields = [wiki:documentation/Glossary#BasicTypes cdata]''' [wiki:documentation/Glossary#CaseInformation (CS)]
  A comma-separated list of fields that this column will fetch from the data source about each row and display.

'''formatter = [wiki:documentation/Glossary#BasicTypes cdata]''' [wiki:documentation/Glossary#CaseInformation (CS)]
  The name of the data formatter to use to turn the raw field information into RML. If not set (or the formatter can't be found) then the raw text will be displayed.

'''width = [wiki:documentation/Glossary#BasicTypes number]''' [wiki:documentation/Glossary#CaseInformation (CN)]
  The width (in px or %) of the column.

== DATASELECT Element ==

The ''DATASELECT'' Element is described in the [wiki:documentation/RML/Forms#DATASELECTElement Forms] section.